This template contains:

--Sass folders and directories suggested archtecture
--A few media queries
--grid class css files
--package json with build tools and dev tools
--tests to check connections with js, css, and image files (just run index file)
--favicon

--------------

To Set up New Git repo for project

Initialize repo in VS Code
Create repo in github and copy url

ctrl ~ for terminal enter these commands

git remote add origin $url goes here$ (looks like git@github.com:tmurvv/take2techsitesass.git)
git push -u origin master

If you keep getting prompted for credentials try:
git config --global credential.helper wincred

---------------
To set up node
go to command prompt ctrl ~ and type npm install to install from existing json file

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
to install manually if no existing json file:

"node -v" to be sure node installed. lists node version
"npm init" creates json file
"npm install node-sass --save-dev" install sass and save reference to json file

for development:
"live-server" is already installed (updates browser with every change automatically)

for build:

"autoprefixer": "^8.3.0",
    "concat": "^1.0.3",
    "node-sass": "^4.8.3",
    "postcss-cli": "^5.0.0"
npm install npm-run-all --save-dev
